As Nigeria Agricultural sector continue to gets global recognition, an Agricultural expert who has been a link between Nigeria and China in Agro business exportation,  Dr Kenechukwu Nnamani, the chief executive officer of Kvas Group, a company that has been involved in various businesses including exportation of Agricultural product from Nigeria to China has revealed that Pork Meat exportation to China is set for arise rise between 2.3 million to 2.6 million tonnes this Year. Dr Nnamani made this known during a chat with some newsmen in Abuja yesterday. According to him, the demand for the product (Pork Meat) by the international market has opened up the piggery market to farmers who are interested in raring the animal. He add that the rise has shown the high demand China has for the Nigerian market. “This is a good development. The Agricultural sector is growing bigger on a daily basis and we are happy that we can contribute to expanding the market. “Pig Farming is on a high demand and the demand will continue to increase as it is. We have set up machineries to work with farmers, ensuring that we can meet the high demand of the product. Pork meat exportation to China is set to rise between 2.3 million to 2.6 million tonnes this year.” Dr Nnamani had been using his China2Nigeria online and offline platform in getting products from verified factories to China. 